args: How many years has it been since we\nperformed in such a large venue?\nI'm practically shaking!
I'm certain it will be fine. ...Ah, look!\nLucretia has arrived!
It's been a long time, Vixel.
I'm glad you decided to put aside your\nstubbornness and perform with me at last.
Thank you for joining us today, Lucretia.\nI am finally ready to do this.
All right, everyone. Deep breaths, now.\nLet's go put on our finest performance.
(And so, the curtain rises once moreâ€”the\nsame one I lowered on myself long ago.)
(This song will echo into my future,\nand I shall guide it with my baton!)
The singing and music were splendid.\nGreat job to you all!
I stood on the stage today because of your\nsupport, Prince!
And with the profits we made tonight,\nthe orchestra can make its comeback!
I really didn't do anything special,\nbut I'm glad to hear it went well.
Oh, that reminds me. Where's Vixel?\nI haven't seen him anywhere.
Say, that's right. I could have sworn he\nwas here this whole time.
I'll go look for him. In the meantime,\nyou should all enjoy the after-party.
Ah. I apologize if I worried you.\nI just wanted to...soak this in.
Truth be told, I didn't believe either myself\nor the orchestra could reach such heights.
Everyone firmly asserted their own sound\nin the face of Lucretia's singing.
And my conducting harmonized those\nsounds and transformed them into a\nbeautiful melody.
I waved my baton as though in a dream,\nall of my earlier fears forgotten.
It's not just Lucretia who has talent...\nI do, too.
I think it's always been that way.
Yes. I was trapped in the idea that my\nabandonment of singing defined me as\nan abject failure.
It probably seems like a simple matter to\nan outsider, but I struggled with it for so\nvery long. How stubborn I was!
For what it's worth, I believed in you and\nthe orchestra right from the start.
Ha! The tables have turned, it seems;\nnow I am the junior coming to YOU\nfor sage advice!
Heh. Maybe so. ...Er, is that all right?
Of course. I was clearly acting like a child\nin this situation.
Ah, I've such a long way to go before I\ntruly grow up.
Huh? What do you mean? After all, today\nyou said goodbye to your past...
Well, I can't be an adult just yet,\nbecause right now I'm as excited\nas a child on Dragonyule.
It's as if I'm a small boy once more,\nbrimming with excitement over the\npossibilities of sound and music!
It seems my adoring fans have arrived.
Um, so what's the deal with you and that\nLucretia woman? Is she your girlfriend?!
Ha ha! No, she is merely an old friend.\nI'm in no relationship at the moment.
Instead, I am adrift in a sea of sound,\nborne aloft by my feelings for music.
I once believed those feelings were not\nreciprocated, but now I realize the music\nactually DOES return them in its own way.
If it's all right, I'd like for you to come\nlisten to me again; I will make the next\nperformance even greater than today's!
When I grow up, I wanna marry Vixel!
He's so cool and grown-up!\nNobody can resist Vixel's charms!
(From now on, I think he's going to\npursue opportunities the way he did\nwhen he was younger.)
(He'll have the composure of an adult,\nbut also the passion of youth.)
You really are a smooth operator, Vixel.
This again? I told you, I have a long\nway yet to go.
Maybeâ€”but there's a lot of coolness\nlumped in with all of that.
My thanks. I will do my best to continue\nbeing worthy of your high opinion.
Today's finale will continue into the music\nI play tomorrow.
I'll continue trying to surpass myself.\nThe music inside me shall never end!
